x4freetext: Time resolution of incident neutrons was equal 6.nsec/m
.Sm-149 sample weighed 41.7 grams and was enriched
Foliated block from moderator and material with large
capture cross section was placed into detector for
carried out by 27.1 eV, 29.7 eV, 49.3 eV resonances
with well-known parameters for Sm-147 and
17.1 eV, 23.2 eV resonances with well-known parameters
Neutron flux energy dependence was taken from
for time independent background of detector,
reactor background connected with delayed and recycled

x4freetext: Data without errors are approximate data.
Radiative capture curves measurements of Sm-144 and
Sm-148 were used for isotopic identification of
observed resonances and for areas normalization of
resonances Sm-147 (by SM-144 curve ) and Sm-149
Refs. YF, SNP, YFI-12, INDC(CCP)-30 were
Updates for current rules and dictionaries.
Data marked as "ALL POINTS ELIMINATED FROM SET"
were re-stored from archive in Subents 002-005,008-009.
Free text in COMMENT was corrected.
STATUS information was updated for new rules.
Sm-147 gamma-widths were taken equal to 50.milli-eV for
resonances in which gamma-width was not determined.
Unresolved resonance. Stated with is sum of
widths of neighboring resonances with flag (1.)
